1. ConfigMap (configuration management)

Right now your app has hardcoded message.

We will move it to Kubernetes.

configmap.yaml

```
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: my-app-config
data:
  APP_MESSAGE: "Hello from Kubernetes ConfigMap 🚀"

```

kubectl apply -f configmap.yaml


app.py

```
import os
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return os.getenv("APP_MESSAGE", "default message")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5000)

```


deployement.yaml

```
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: my-app
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: my-app
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: my-app
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: my-app
          image: my-app:latest
          imagePullPolicy: Never
          ports:
            - containerPort: 5000
          env:
            - name: APP_MESSAGE
              valueFrom:
                configMapKeyRef:
                  name: my-app-config
                  key: APP_MESSAGE
            - name: SECRET_TOKEN
              valueFrom:
                secretKeyRef:
                  name: my-app-secret
                  key: SECRET_TOKEN

```


eval $(minikube docker-env)
docker build -t my-app:latest .
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml


minikube service my-app-service

you should see - Hello from Kubernetes ConfigMap 🚀



2. Kubernetes Secret

Now move sensitive data from Jenkins → Kubernetes.

```
Create secret.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: my-app-secret
type: Opaque
data:
  SECRET_TOKEN: c3VwZXItc2VjcmV0
```
👉 That value is base64 of:

super-secret



kubectl apply -f secret.yaml


add to deployement.yaml
```
env:
  - name: APP_MESSAGE
    valueFrom:
      configMapKeyRef:
        name: my-app-config
        key: APP_MESSAGE
  - name: SECRET_TOKEN
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: my-app-secret
        key: SECRET_TOKEN
```
add to app.py
```
@app.route("/secret")
def secret():
    return os.getenv("SECRET_TOKEN", "no secret")
```


